post_text: Congratulations to our uber-talented art teacher, Sabina Bolinger! We’re so proud of you!
shared_text:
Kansas Art Education Association
August 22 at 9:52 PM ·

Sabina Bollinger - Outstanding K-12 Art
The 2020 Outstanding K-12 Art Educator is Sabina Bollinger of Madison-Vergil Public Schools. Her most notable accomplishments include teaching a dual credit course of Graphic Design through FHTC Technical College and planning, organizing, and setting up a league art show yearly that’s held at Emporia State University. She has also published the articles “Handbuilt Hang-Outs” and “Portraiture: A Study of Greek Gods.” She has also served as a KAEA/NAEA member and a member of the MEA (Madison Education Association) as a member of her teacher’s association and currently is on the scholarship committee.
#ksarted #kaeaawards #naeagowest

post_text: Good evening, Bulldog families of 7-12th graders! We look forward to seeing our Madison High and Junior High School students on Thursday, and just wanted to share a few bits of information with you. Thursday will start with student class meetings, so that we can update students on what the day to day happenings will look like. All students ARE required to wear a mask, and a cloth Madison mask will be provided to students who would like one. Any student who does not ride the bus to school will need to enter through the South doors, by the new gym. Students who are bussed will enter through the West doors. If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to call 437-2909. Thanks, and have a great evening!

post_text:
Attention 5th grade Parents and Students:
Mrs. McDonald will be hosting a Beginning Band Night on Tuesday, August 18th from 5-6:30 in front of the Elementary School

She will be there to answer any questions you may have. Flint Hills Music will have the books and supplies your students will need for band as well as instruments for rent or purchase if anyone is interested.

Students may use an instrument you already own, rent an instrument from the school, purchase an instrument, or rent to own from the music store. Along with an instrument students need a book and either reeds, oil, or sticks and cleaning supplies.

post_text: We will have EZSchoolPay available for school enrollment fees this year! We ask that you do not add any enrollment fees to your cart without help from a staff member. If you would like to pay your student’s enrollment fees by debit or credit card, please be sure to have your parent account set up prior to enrollment, so that we can get you checked out quickly. If you have not already set up an account, please email kcrooks@usd386.net for your student’s school ID number. (You will need this in order to connect your student to your parent account.) Do not hesitate to call 437-2909, should you have any questions. *** Please be aware that there is a $3 processing fee, charged by the company that runs the app.

Bulldog Nation,
The Madison After Prom Committee will be sponsoring a prom for the 2020 Juniors and Seniors on Saturday, August 1st. Please plan to line Mainstreet to support them as they parade through town. Juniors and Seniors will congregate at the high school parking lot and begin parading at 6pm with an ending destination of the Madison Sauder Center. Community members are encouraged to make their way to the Sauder Center to watch the kids as they promenade into the building where they will enjoy a catered meal, DJ, dance and PRIZES!
*note to Juniors and Seniors: Formal attire is optional

shared_text:
Greenwood County Health Department
February 13 at 10:56 AM ·

We have known cases of Influenza types A & B in our county. Here are some ways to prevent spreading the Flu or catching it.

Prevention- Everyday actions to stop the spread of Influenza and the Common Cold

*Avoid close contact with sick people
* If you have the flu, stay home for five days following onset of
symptoms or until fever free for 24 hours
*People with influenza are considered infectious for 5-7 days
after becoming sick
*Cover your nose and mouth with a tissue when you cough or
sneeze
*Wash your hands often with soap and water or use alcohol-
based hand cleaners
*Avoid touching your eyes, nose or mouth. Germs spread this
way.
*Clean and disinfect surfaces and objects that may be
contaminated with proper cleaning products and let set wet
for at least 10 minutes before drying surfaces

Please share to stop the spread!

Josie, Hunter, and Casey competed in Job Interview. Josie placed 6th and Hunter was 9th overall in the A division, and placed 4th as a team! Casey placed 5th overall in the B division!

It was a great day for the Bulldogs!

Beth Gaines is with Sam Davis and 5 others.
January 25 at 8:34 PM ·

It's been my belief that in this life, what you receive is directly proportional to the effort applied. That said, you can expect big things from the newly established agricultural education program and their FFA chapter in Madison. Tonight the room was packed for their first fundraising dinner! The community support was amazing. Can't wait to see what they can accomplish!
